Post.create! title: "Overheard at Space Center Houston", body:"Dinosaurs are extinct today because they lacked opposable thumbs and the brainpower to build a space program.

Across the sea of space, the stars are other suns.

That's one small step for [a] man, one giant leap for mankind.

Here men from the planet Earth first set foot upon the Moon. July 1969 AD. We came in peace for all mankind.

Science has not yet mastered prophecy. We predict too much for the next year and yet far too little for the next 10."

Post.create! title: "Overheard at The Black Lab", body: " Never, never assume that what you have achieved is fucking good enough. The details are not the details. They make the fucking design. Widows and orphans are terrible fucking tragedies, both in real life and definitely in typography. If you fucking give up, you will achieve nothing. While having drinks with Tibor Kalman one night, he told me, &ldquo;When you make something no one hates, no one fucking loves it.&rdquo;

Remember it’s called the creative process, it’s not the creative fucking moment. Nothing of value comes to you without fucking working at it. Think about all the fucking possibilities. Practice won’t get you anywhere if you mindlessly fucking practice the same thing. Change only occurs when you work deliberately with purpose toward a goal. Make your work consistent but not fucking predictable. You won’t get good at anything by doing it a lot fucking aimlessly. Remember it’s called the creative process, it’s not the creative fucking moment. Remember it’s called the creative process, it’s not the creative fucking moment.

A good fucking composition is the result of a hierarchy consisting of clearly contrasting elements set with distinct alignments containing irregular intervals of negative space. Design as if your fucking life depended on it. To surpass others is fucking tough, if you only do as you are told you don’t have it in you to succeed. Never let your guard down by thinking you’re fucking good enough.

Saul Bass on failure: Failure is built into creativity… the creative act involves this element of ‘newness’ and ‘experimentalism,’ then one must expect and accept the fucking possibility of failure. Don’t worry about what other people fucking think. The details are not the details. They make the fucking design. Never, never assume that what you have achieved is fucking good enough. When you sit down to work, external critics aren’t the enemy. It’s you who you must to fight against to do great fucking work. You must overcome yourself. Don’t worry about what other people fucking think.

Respect your fucking craft. Sometimes it is appropriate to place various typographic elements on the outside of the fucking left margin of text to maintain a strong vertical axis. This practice is referred to as exdenting and is most often used with bullets and quotations. Don’t fucking lie to yourself. Respect your fucking craft. Design is all about fucking relationships&mdash;the relationship of form and content, the relationship of elements, the relationship  of designer and user.

"
